1
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:04,463
(roaring)

2
00:00:04,463 --> 00:00:07,925
Now that the devastating monster
Yamigedo has been revived,

3
00:00:07,925 --> 00:00:10,010
the only way to seal
him away again is with

4
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:12,679
the power of the
eight Omni Lords.

5
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:16,350
It's up to us to find them,
and there's only one way we can.

6
00:00:16,350 --> 00:00:19,144
‐We gotta Buddyfight!
‐We gotta Buddyfight!

7
00:00:19,144 --> 00:00:21,313
Prominence burst!

8
00:00:21,313 --> 00:00:22,481
Ahhh!

9
00:00:22,481 --> 00:00:25,442
Okay, boss, I'm leaving
the rest to you.

10
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:27,027
Understood.

11
00:00:27,027 --> 00:00:28,779
Might be my adrenaline talking,

12
00:00:28,779 --> 00:00:31,240
but try and cut Gao
some slack, huh?

13
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:35,327
I will, and I'll start
by giving him the victory.

14
00:00:35,327 --> 00:00:37,663
♪

15
00:00:37,663 --> 00:00:40,541
Deela Column!

16
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:43,168
♪

17
00:00:43,168 --> 00:00:45,379
Is this some kind of attack?

18
00:00:45,379 --> 00:00:48,799
Oh, it feels so warm.

19
00:00:48,799 --> 00:02:17,095
♪

20
00:02:22,267 --> 00:02:26,605
♪

21
00:02:26,605 --> 00:02:28,940
Tomorrow's a big day.

22
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:32,069
At the next Buddyfight Club,
Tasuku will fight me,

23
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:35,113
and if I win, I will
take his Buddy monster,

24
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:37,282
the Star Guardian, Jackknife.

25
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:39,951
It's crazy, me helping
that criminal Death Shido

26
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,912
after all she's done to Gao.

27
00:02:41,912 --> 00:02:45,165
Imagine all this time
it was Sofia Sakharov,

28
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:49,378
and in order to save her I have
to risk losing you, Jack.

29
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:52,631
♪

30
00:02:52,631 --> 00:02:55,550
Don't worry, I know
you can take this guy.

31
00:02:55,550 --> 00:02:57,678
I'm your Buddy and
I stand behind you.

32
00:02:57,678 --> 00:03:01,598
Thanks for saying that, but
I can't help thinking...

33
00:03:01,598 --> 00:03:04,893
What'll happen if
you don't beat Suzaku?

34
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:07,145
That can't happen,
I won't lose you again!

35
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:10,941
There are no guarantees in life.

36
00:03:10,941 --> 00:03:14,027
That's right, the amazing
Variable Cord lets you put

37
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:17,239
as many of your held cards
as you like into his soul!

38
00:03:17,239 --> 00:03:19,074
You think I should
back out of the fight?

39
00:03:19,074 --> 00:03:21,159
This is no time
to doubt yourself.

40
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:24,246
There must be another way, why
should I have to sacrifice you,

41
00:03:24,246 --> 00:03:27,499
Jack, all for that
self‐serving Sofia Sakharov?

42
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:29,876
But think of the bigger picture.

43
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:34,047
Questioning her will give us
valuable intel on Yamigedo.

44
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:35,590
Yeah, you're right.

45
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:38,844
It's just so unfair.

46
00:03:38,844 --> 00:03:41,930
(yelling)

47
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:44,182
♪

48
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:45,475
What's wrong?

49
00:03:45,475 --> 00:03:48,979
Speak to me, Jack, Jack!

50
00:03:56,778 --> 00:04:00,198
That Neodragon, Star Guardian,
Jackknife should be experiencing

51
00:04:00,198 --> 00:04:03,535
the consequences of his
transformation about now.

52
00:04:03,535 --> 00:04:07,956
And if truth be told, he
doesn't have much time left.

53
00:04:07,956 --> 00:04:10,208
What're you saying, Suzaku?

54
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:12,794
Unlike you guys, he didn't
go through the necessary

55
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:15,464
safeguarding in Star Dragon
World that allows him

56
00:04:15,464 --> 00:04:17,549
to function in other worlds.

57
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:20,218
Then his systems are
under significant stress.

58
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,929
Yes, there's no doubt about it.

59
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:25,223
What are you going to do?

60
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:28,852
Leave him be.

61
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:30,687
I'm only joking.

62
00:04:30,687 --> 00:04:34,483
♪

63
00:04:34,483 --> 00:04:37,736
Well, his only hope is to
return to Star Dragon World

64
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:40,238
and to receive
proper maintenance.

65
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,948
We understand.

66
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:45,827
Hold that thought.

67
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:49,831
They're onto us.

68
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,917
Let him go.

69
00:04:51,917 --> 00:04:54,920
He is of no threat to us.

70
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,963
Hm.

71
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:59,257
What do you mean you
don't know what's wrong?

72
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:02,761
Jack is wasting away
before our very eyes!

73
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:05,347
How can you not know
the cause of his pain?

74
00:05:05,347 --> 00:05:07,015
Well, Star Guardian, Jackknife

75
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:09,392
is sort of a
mechanical life form.

76
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:12,729
Workings of his body are
a complete mystery to us.

77
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:16,107
There are just too many things
that we don't yet understand.

78
00:05:16,107 --> 00:05:18,026
(phone ringing)

79
00:05:18,026 --> 00:05:22,864
That's strange, I'm
receiving a call for you.

80
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:24,616
It's Rouga Aragami.

81
00:05:24,616 --> 00:05:26,117
You've got nerve!

82
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:29,120
Is it me, or do you seem
more uptight than usual?

83
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,040
Nothing's happened
to your Buddy, has it?

84
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,291
What do you know about it?

85
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:35,043
I thought I'd repay
my debt to you

86
00:05:35,043 --> 00:05:37,712
by rescuing Sofia
from Suzaku Kenran.

87
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:41,258
So I sent my Buddy to scout a
way out of Cho Nagoya Castle.

88
00:05:41,258 --> 00:05:43,844
That's when he heard the
news that your Buddy Jack

89
00:05:43,844 --> 00:05:45,846
isn't long for this world.

90
00:05:45,846 --> 00:05:47,806
That's not true,
that's impossible!

91
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,641
Kenran said something else.

92
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:51,726
You must return Jack
to Star Dragon World

93
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:54,479
so he can go through
some kind of maintenance.

94
00:05:54,479 --> 00:05:57,566
If you don't, he's a goner.

95
00:05:57,566 --> 00:06:00,193
I'll do whatever I have
to do to save him.

96
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:08,493
♪

97
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:12,163
Suzaku Kenran, come on out,
I wanna talk to you!

98
00:06:12,163 --> 00:06:14,541
‐You know why I'm here!
‐Relax.

99
00:06:14,541 --> 00:06:16,543
Why are you yelling?

100
00:06:16,543 --> 00:06:20,088
So, what brings you here so
terribly early in the morning?

101
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:22,507
Don't tell me you're here to
beg me to cancel our fight

102
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:25,510
with Star Guardian,
Jackknife as the prize?

103
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,971
I made it quite clear
what would happen to that

104
00:06:27,971 --> 00:06:32,183
deceitful girlfriend of yours
if we don't do battle.

105
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:35,896
I came here to ask,
please save Jack.

106
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:38,857
What do you mean, what's
the matter with him?

107
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:40,859
He's gotta go to
Star Dragon World

108
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:43,361
or else the unthinkable
will happen.

109
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:47,282
‐Don't play dumb.
‐So, you know about that.

110
00:06:47,282 --> 00:06:48,742
I do.

111
00:06:48,742 --> 00:06:53,580
Do you even know what
Star Dragon World is?

112
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:55,498
Star Dragon World?

113
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:58,376
It's a planet with a highly
advanced civilization,

114
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,170
and it lies far, far away.

115
00:07:00,170 --> 00:07:03,214
Not exactly, but I know
it lies far away from here.

116
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:06,801
True, but Star Dragon World
is not just a vast distance

117
00:07:06,801 --> 00:07:09,763
from Earth in proximity of
place, but also in time.

118
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:13,141
You see, it's the future
reality of Dragon World.

119
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:16,102
The future, what do you mean?

120
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,730
Are you saying that you
come from the future?

121
00:07:18,730 --> 00:07:20,857
That's right, long ago

122
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:23,568
when the heartless beast
Yamigedo spearheaded

123
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:26,154
the Hundred Demons Army
in a merciless assault

124
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:29,115
on the universe, destroying
countless worlds,

125
00:07:29,115 --> 00:07:32,118
the Armordeity, Dynamis,
was forced to act.

126
00:07:32,118 --> 00:07:35,080
Her desperate search for
individuals worthy of becoming

127
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:37,916
Omni Lords required her
to travel through time

128
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,585
to the distant future's
version of Dragon World,

129
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:43,088
known as Star Dragon World.

130
00:07:43,088 --> 00:07:46,633
There she found me and brought
me here to your time.

131
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:50,970
‐So you're‐‐
‐I am.

132
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:55,308
You're the Sixth Omni
Storm Lord, Variable Cord!

133
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:59,187
Suzaku Kenran is an identity
I created to live incognito

134
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:02,273
amongst you humans, and
I started Buddyfight Club

135
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:05,985
to attract and meet this world's
most powerful Buddyfighters.

136
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:08,321
♪

137
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:09,948
But for what purpose?

138
00:08:09,948 --> 00:08:12,617
To help in our crusade
against Yamigedo.

139
00:08:12,617 --> 00:08:15,453
The only way we can ensure
sealing him away again

140
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,455
is by befriending and recruiting

141
00:08:17,455 --> 00:08:21,418
the number one
Buddyfighters in this world.

142
00:08:21,418 --> 00:08:25,046
I'm curious, would you allow
me to join such a cause?

143
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:28,550
Hm, you rank yourself one of
the most powerful Buddyfighters

144
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:30,719
‐on Earth?
‐Yes, and I'll prove it

145
00:08:30,719 --> 00:08:33,096
by defeating you at
your next club meeting,

146
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:36,599
but not without Jack.

147
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:38,893
So we have to get Jack
to Star Dragon World

148
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,562
to get him the help he needs.

149
00:08:40,562 --> 00:08:42,772
I will agree on one condition.

150
00:08:42,772 --> 00:08:45,233
Here we go.

151
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:48,153
You must let me win the fight.

152
00:08:48,153 --> 00:08:50,488
I have my reputation
and cover to uphold.

153
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:53,283
As you know, I've never
lost a match, and though

154
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:56,494
I can't imagine that I'd ever
lose to someone like you,

155
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:59,789
I've learned that you humans
are full of surprises.

156
00:08:59,789 --> 00:09:03,710
Hang on a sec, you're telling
me to throw the fight?

157
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,504
Yes, well I guess that's
one way of putting it.

158
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:08,423
Good, it's agreed.

159
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:11,468
♪

160
00:09:11,468 --> 00:09:16,222
It's so weird, why is
this happening to Jack?

161
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,391
(whooshing noise)

162
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,685
Tasuku!

163
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:24,022
Why did you leave me and
come here by yourself?

164
00:09:24,022 --> 00:09:26,024
I didn't want to.

165
00:09:26,024 --> 00:09:28,193
I just don't know what to do!

166
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:31,446
I need your advice, help me!

167
00:09:31,446 --> 00:09:34,365
He really asked you
to lose on purpose?

168
00:09:34,365 --> 00:09:36,451
I just don't see the point.

169
00:09:36,451 --> 00:09:39,662
Why would Variable Cord want me
to let him win if he's looking

170
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:43,166
for the most powerful
Buddyfighter in the world?

171
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,376
I wish I had an answer for you.

172
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:48,379
Either way, you can't
give in to his demands.

173
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:51,549
But if I don't do what he
wants, you know what'll happen.

174
00:09:51,549 --> 00:09:54,052
Don't let that
influence your decision.

175
00:09:54,052 --> 00:09:57,514
I'd prefer to have my
remaining hours lived honorably.

176
00:09:57,514 --> 00:10:00,725
‐Are you sure?
‐Listen,

177
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,061
let's defeat Kenran together.

178
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:06,189
Think of it as my last wish.

179
00:10:06,189 --> 00:10:09,317
What I want most in the
waning moments of my time

180
00:10:09,317 --> 00:10:13,863
is to fight alongside
you as your Buddy.

181
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:23,081
♪

182
00:10:23,081 --> 00:10:25,750
The first rule
of Buddyfight Club,

183
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:28,795
you do not talk
about Buddyfight Club!

184
00:10:28,795 --> 00:10:33,383
The second rule, you do not
talk about Buddyfight Club!

185
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:37,929
The third rule, when betting
on a fight, the stakes must be

186
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:40,640
whatever you value
most in your life.

187
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:44,102
The fourth rule, the winner
can do whatever they want

188
00:10:44,102 --> 00:10:46,729
with the loser's most
prized possessions.

189
00:10:46,729 --> 00:10:49,649
The fifth rule, if
you win five fights,

190
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:53,319
you earn the right to
challenge Suzaku Kenran!

191
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:54,988
I feel like I'm going to cry.

192
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:57,031
The big day has finally arrived!

193
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:59,659
In the circle of destiny
sits the beautiful young girl

194
00:10:59,659 --> 00:11:01,411
who infiltrated our last meeting

195
00:11:01,411 --> 00:11:03,246
under the guise of Death Shido.

196
00:11:03,246 --> 00:11:07,208
And our very own Suzaku Kenran
will fight Tasuku Ryuenji

197
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:09,627
of the Buddy Police
to decide her fate.

198
00:11:09,627 --> 00:11:13,548
The first‐ever Star Dragon World
battle is about to begin!

199
00:11:13,548 --> 00:11:15,466
We have an expanded audience.

200
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:17,635
I better put on a good show.

201
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:19,804
Twinkling stars that
light the cosmos,

202
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:23,308
dance like an electric
storm and unite as one.

203
00:11:23,308 --> 00:11:27,020
Luminize Gorgeous Galaxy.

204
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:30,398
Unite Elite Warriors
of the future,

205
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:32,108
bringing evolution!

206
00:11:32,108 --> 00:11:33,318
Luminize!

207
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:34,986
‐Time to raise the flag.
‐Time to raise the flag.

208
00:11:34,986 --> 00:11:39,115
‐I'm with Star Dragon World.
‐I'm with Star Dragon World too.

209
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:41,367
♪

210
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:44,412
‐You okay?
‐Yeah, I'm fine.

211
00:11:44,412 --> 00:11:47,123
The first move goes to
Tasuku of the Buddy Police.

212
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:50,251
He calls Photon Crown,
Geocorona to the center

213
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:52,337
who attacks, causing two damage!

214
00:11:52,337 --> 00:11:54,589
Draw, charge and draw.

215
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:57,842
I call Brun Deus,
Akision to the left.

216
00:11:57,842 --> 00:12:01,346
Azul Deus, Tesslamagna
to the right position.

217
00:12:01,346 --> 00:12:06,017
And lastly, I call Vert Deus,
Matrix to the center.

218
00:12:06,017 --> 00:12:09,854
Suzaku starts out with his
tried and true formation.

219
00:12:09,854 --> 00:12:12,023
He destroys Geocorona,
but the move ends

220
00:12:12,023 --> 00:12:14,359
with Tasuku still
at ten life points.

221
00:12:14,359 --> 00:12:17,111
Tasuku responds with some
draw spells to put more cards

222
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,072
in his hand, then
calls Shadowscare

223
00:12:19,072 --> 00:12:21,282
and Buddy Calls Jackknife!

224
00:12:21,282 --> 00:12:23,910
(background chatter)

225
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:27,038
Okay, let's crossnize.

226
00:12:27,038 --> 00:12:28,498
You heard right!

227
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:32,085
Crossnize is a unique ability
to Star Dragon World monsters.

228
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:34,837
Fighters can use this super
skill to put Dragonarms

229
00:12:34,837 --> 00:12:38,049
in the card's soul
to get new powers.

230
00:12:38,049 --> 00:12:40,677
Dragonarms loading.

231
00:12:40,677 --> 00:12:43,721
Roll shift, variant form.

232
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:46,557
All devices engage.

233
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:48,768
SES active.

234
00:12:48,768 --> 00:12:50,812
Load finished.

235
00:12:50,812 --> 00:12:52,981
♪

236
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:55,358
Cavalier Sword!

237
00:12:55,358 --> 00:12:57,443
♪

238
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,487
‐You sure?
‐We have to,

239
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:01,823
and stop worrying!

240
00:13:01,823 --> 00:13:03,700
I pay one gauge and one life,

241
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:06,536
and I equip Star
Saber, Asteroid!

242
00:13:06,536 --> 00:13:08,413
♪

243
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:11,374
Shadowscare and Jack,
do a link attack!

244
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:13,710
Yes, my master.

245
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,712
Vision Nailer!

246
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:18,923
Cavalier Sword!

247
00:13:18,923 --> 00:13:20,925
Penetrate!

248
00:13:20,925 --> 00:13:26,639
♪

249
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:29,309
I cast Earth Barrier.

250
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:33,104
Ha, are you just about to
stand by and let Jackknife go?

251
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:35,606
♪

252
00:13:35,606 --> 00:13:38,151
‐Matrix.
‐Yes, master?

253
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:41,738
I know your mind very well.

254
00:13:41,738 --> 00:13:44,907
(shouting)

255
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,117
Disarm!

256
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:49,120
Jackknife revives
using Soulguard!

257
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:52,623
(grunting)

258
00:13:52,623 --> 00:13:54,333
Poor Jack.

259
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:58,296
‐Tesslamagna.
‐We are sworn to protect Suzaku.

260
00:13:58,296 --> 00:14:01,132
All those who oppose
him will be destroyed.

261
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:04,302
(explosive noises)

262
00:14:04,302 --> 00:14:06,220
‐Akision.
‐Understood.

263
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,431
Commencing attack maneuvers.

264
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:13,269
♪

265
00:14:13,269 --> 00:14:14,687
End of move.

266
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:17,940
I will activate an ability
and then draw three cards.

267
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:21,903
And Suzaku continues to
replenish the cards in his hand.

268
00:14:21,903 --> 00:14:25,531
I draw, charge and draw.

269
00:14:25,531 --> 00:14:30,161
I cast Sudden Wormhole!

270
00:14:30,161 --> 00:14:32,330
That timely spell
card lets Tasuku

271
00:14:32,330 --> 00:14:34,415
call a monster
from the drop zone.

272
00:14:34,415 --> 00:14:37,668
I call Shadowscare from
the drop zone to the left.

273
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:40,713
‐Time to shine!
‐Attack with me.

274
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:42,632
You're the boss.

275
00:14:42,632 --> 00:14:46,511
‐Star Saber, Asteroid!
‐Vision Nailer!

276
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:49,388
Okay, Jack, I want you
to go after the fighter.

277
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:53,101
Right, Star Blade Terminate!

278
00:14:53,101 --> 00:14:57,688
♪

279
00:14:57,688 --> 00:15:00,691
‐End of move.
‐So how you holding up, Jack?

280
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:03,319
‐Your move.
‐I draw.

281
00:15:03,319 --> 00:15:04,821
Charge and draw.

282
00:15:04,821 --> 00:15:06,656
If I didn't know
about our agreement

283
00:15:06,656 --> 00:15:08,783
I'd say you're
trying to beat me.

284
00:15:08,783 --> 00:15:12,286
I knew you'd be far too honest
to engage in deception,

285
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:14,831
but I did tell you I couldn't
imagine losing to someone

286
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:17,917
like you, and now
I'm sure that I won't.

287
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:19,836
Play time is over.

288
00:15:19,836 --> 00:15:23,881
I pay two gauge and Buddy
Call to the center...

289
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:27,426
Sixth Omni Storm
Lord, Variable Cord.

290
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:30,888
♪

291
00:15:30,888 --> 00:15:33,724
Suzaku's called his
Buddy, Variable Cord!

292
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,394
This has the potential
to get nasty, gentlemen!

293
00:15:36,394 --> 00:15:40,022
I place my nine held cards
into Variable Cord's soul.

294
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:43,192
♪

295
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:45,570
Amazing, look at that!

296
00:15:45,570 --> 00:15:49,740
Four Elgar Cannons, Four
Divisigators, and One Vogel!

297
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:52,827
All nine cards in his
hand are Dragonarms!

298
00:15:52,827 --> 00:15:56,956
Variable Cord has 15,000
power and 10,000 defense!

299
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:59,917
Not to mention a knock‐up
critical of seven.

300
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:02,211
Then I guess my fate is sealed.

301
00:16:02,211 --> 00:16:05,339
Variable Cord,
attack the fighter

302
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,759
with Variable Typhoon!

303
00:16:08,759 --> 00:16:12,680
♪

304
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:16,142
(screaming)

305
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:18,811
In the blink of an eye
he's reduced to two life.

306
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:21,272
And Akision's closing
in to clean up.

307
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:24,775
I cast (unintelligible) Bullet!

308
00:16:24,775 --> 00:16:25,943
He pays one gauge,

309
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:28,237
and desperately fires
off a counter spell.

310
00:16:28,237 --> 00:16:31,824
He can destroy one monster
with 3,000 defense or less.

311
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,826
I cast an Akision.

312
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:35,995
(explosive noises)

313
00:16:35,995 --> 00:16:38,247
He's rather persistent
for a human.

314
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,374
He leaves me no choice.

315
00:16:40,374 --> 00:16:44,754
‐Tesslamagna.
‐I will destroy him!

316
00:16:44,754 --> 00:16:47,757
End of move, your move.

317
00:16:47,757 --> 00:16:50,509
Draw, charge and draw!

318
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:54,138
How can you keep going when
your Buddy's suffering so?

319
00:16:54,138 --> 00:16:57,016
(groaning)

320
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:59,644
He's right, what am I gonna do?

321
00:16:59,644 --> 00:17:02,021
Oh, it's like a deer in
the headlights out there.

322
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,147
Is he injured?

323
00:17:03,147 --> 00:17:05,524
Maybe he's not happy with
the cards in his hand.

324
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,818
My guess is Suzaku
somehow forced him

325
00:17:07,818 --> 00:17:09,820
into throwing the
fight to save Jack.

326
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:12,281
‐You think so?
‐But he's too noble

327
00:17:12,281 --> 00:17:16,494
for such dishonorable schemes
and is having second thoughts.

328
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:18,829
Will he do it?

329
00:17:18,829 --> 00:17:21,666
Tasuku, we agreed,

330
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:25,836
you won't let my condition
sway your principles.

331
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:28,297
Letting emotions
affect your decisions

332
00:17:28,297 --> 00:17:30,174
is never the right choice.

333
00:17:30,174 --> 00:17:32,510
‐But Jack‐‐
‐I tell you this,

334
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:35,137
if you choose to throw
this fight for my sake,

335
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:39,517
then I can't continue to
be your Buddy any longer.

336
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:42,144
You mean you'd
really perish for me?

337
00:17:46,524 --> 00:17:50,194
It's my wish to be your
Buddy until the end.

338
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,280
Then you will be.

339
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,866
I will honor you, and fight in
a way that will make you proud.

340
00:17:55,866 --> 00:17:59,328
I call Dragonarms,
Artiliger to the center!

341
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:01,539
♪

342
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:04,542
That's my Buddy,
Tasuku out there!

343
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:06,877
Time to crossnize!

344
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:09,046
Dragonarms loading.

345
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:12,883
Roll shift, variant form.

346
00:18:12,883 --> 00:18:16,178
All devices engage.

347
00:18:16,178 --> 00:18:18,389
SES active.

348
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,726
Load finished.

349
00:18:21,726 --> 00:18:24,103
Artillerail‐gun!

350
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:26,689
Looks like he means business.

351
00:18:26,689 --> 00:18:29,525
By crossnizing with Artiliger,
Jack gains the power

352
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:32,403
to neutralize the abilities
of all monsters he faces

353
00:18:32,403 --> 00:18:35,948
that are size two or smaller.

354
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,534
‐Let him have it, Jack!
‐Right!

355
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:41,829
You risk much if you continue
down this path, young man.

356
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:44,915
I know, Jack, let's
do a link attack!

357
00:18:44,915 --> 00:18:47,501
Artillerail‐gun!

358
00:18:47,501 --> 00:18:50,254
(screaming)

359
00:18:50,254 --> 00:18:52,673
Unbelievable, this
kid just wiped out

360
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:55,635
Variable Cord with
a beautiful link attack!

361
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:58,554
Is it history in the making,
Suzaku's first loss?

362
00:18:58,554 --> 00:19:00,723
That's as close as
you're going to get.

363
00:19:00,723 --> 00:19:03,559
I'm not done, final phase!

364
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:05,102
‐But how?
‐Excellent.

365
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:08,814
Show it to me, let me
see your new impact.

366
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:11,942
The light that blazes
a path to the future.

367
00:19:11,942 --> 00:19:14,945
Edge of the soaring star!

368
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,781
Impact!

369
00:19:16,781 --> 00:19:19,659
♪

370
00:19:19,659 --> 00:19:23,829
Radiant Punisher!

371
00:19:23,829 --> 00:19:26,374
(explosions)

372
00:19:26,374 --> 00:19:28,668
♪

373
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:32,129
Game over, winner,
Tasuku Ryuenji.

374
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,964
If I didn't see it,
I wouldn't believe it.

375
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:37,718
An impact for the ages, remember
the name Tasuku Ryuenji!

376
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:41,138
The first and only fighter
to beat Suzaku Kenran!

377
00:19:41,138 --> 00:19:43,808
There are two sides
to every coin, Tasuku.

378
00:19:43,808 --> 00:19:46,143
This time you lost the toss.

379
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:48,604
(background chatter)

380
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:50,189
Jack!

381
00:19:50,189 --> 00:19:52,608
Speak to me, hold on, pal!

382
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:55,277
Jack, come on, please wake up!

383
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:57,405
You fought well, Tasuku.

384
00:19:57,405 --> 00:19:59,031
You have convinced me.

385
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:02,993
You are no doubt one of the
world's best Buddyfighters.

386
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:07,248
♪

387
00:20:07,248 --> 00:20:09,041
This day keeps getting weirder!

388
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,669
Suzaku's just changed
into Variable Cord!

389
00:20:11,669 --> 00:20:14,004
I may be going out on a limb,
but does this mean he's been

390
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:17,299
the Sixth Omni Storm Lord,
Variable Cord all along?

391
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:19,969
In my exhaustive search for
the most powerful Buddyfighter

392
00:20:19,969 --> 00:20:22,179
on your planet, I was
watching for someone

393
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:24,348
who not only possessed
physical potency,

394
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:26,934
but demonstrated strength
of character as well.

395
00:20:26,934 --> 00:20:30,271
If you were one composed of
weak resolve who went along

396
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:33,357
with my tainted back room
offer to throw the fight

397
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:35,693
I would never lend you my power.

398
00:20:35,693 --> 00:20:37,737
For this, I commend you.

399
00:20:37,737 --> 00:20:39,363
Do you mean that you're gonna‐‐

400
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:41,282
Let us create a
bond of friendship

401
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:43,284
to seal Yamigedo together.

402
00:20:43,284 --> 00:20:45,870
Sure, but let's help Jack first!

403
00:20:45,870 --> 00:20:47,747
As you wish.

404
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:50,624
♪

405
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,334
‐Rouga.
‐What is it?

406
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:55,087
Tell me, what would you do if
you were in Tasuku's shoes?

407
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:56,589
Would you have done
the same as him

408
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:58,716
and risked your Buddy's life?

409
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:01,886
‐What do you think?
‐Hm.

410
00:21:01,886 --> 00:21:04,972
‐You humans are so gullible.
‐Huh?

411
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:06,807
We were about to lose patience.

412
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:09,143
We've been waiting thousands
of years for Star Guardian,

413
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:12,229
Jackknife to appear before us.

414
00:21:12,229 --> 00:21:14,231
Once we're sent
to the distant past,

415
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,859
what will happen to us
after we seal Yamigedo?

416
00:21:16,859 --> 00:21:19,695
You shall have to remain
living in that world.

417
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:22,072
After we complete this
monumental task for you,

418
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:24,784
you won't even let us
return to Star Dragon World?

419
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:27,745
Fear not, one day I will
send you a Neodragon

420
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:30,831
that holds the ability
to travel through time.

421
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:33,125
♪

422
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:36,295
And Jack is that dragon.

423
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:38,088
He can't!

424
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:44,261
♪

425
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:46,639
Jack, what're you doing to him?

426
00:21:46,639 --> 00:21:47,890
Isn't is obvious?

427
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:50,601
I'm going to use his ability
to travel through time.

428
00:21:50,601 --> 00:21:52,645
I regret that it will
be impossible for me

429
00:21:52,645 --> 00:21:55,105
to return him to you though.

430
00:21:55,105 --> 00:21:57,274
Your Buddy's time
has come to an end.

431
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:59,443
The stress of traveling
to the future won't be kind

432
00:21:59,443 --> 00:22:01,320
to him in his frail condition.

433
00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,697
I'm sorry things
worked out this way.

434
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:05,282
No, you can't!

435
00:22:05,282 --> 00:22:08,494
I bid Earth farewell as
I head back to the future.

436
00:22:08,494 --> 00:22:11,163
We'll leave Yamigedo
to you this time.

437
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:21,715
♪

438
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:23,801
Variable Cord, no!

439
00:22:23,801 --> 00:22:26,178
At least arrest that girl!

440
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:34,979
♪

441
00:22:34,979 --> 00:22:38,107
This isn't over, I know
that Jack's still alive,

442
00:22:38,107 --> 00:22:40,609
and I'll do whatever
it takes to get him back,

443
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:43,279
even if it means
traveling to the future.

444
00:22:43,279 --> 00:22:47,616
Jack is my Buddy, and I'll
never give up on him.

445
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:52,830
Welcome to Tasuku's
Buddy Police 101.

446
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:54,748
Today I'm gonna tell you
all about the monsters

447
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:56,667
Akision, Tesslamagna,
and Matrix!

448
00:22:56,667 --> 00:22:58,502
‐I'm down!
‐Together, these three

449
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:01,130
Neodragons are capable
of extraordinary power.

450
00:23:01,130 --> 00:23:03,799
When Akision, Tesslamagna,
or Matrix are together

451
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,843
on the field, the fighter
using them is allowed

452
00:23:05,843 --> 00:23:07,845
to draw one card at
the end of their turn.

453
00:23:07,845 --> 00:23:10,431
‐Are you serious?
‐So if all three of these guys

454
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:13,559
are around at the end of your
turn, you can draw three cards.

455
00:23:13,559 --> 00:23:16,353
Which could become six,
then nine, then‐‐

456
00:23:16,353 --> 00:23:18,981
a little help, teach?

457
00:23:18,981 --> 00:24:47,194
♪

458
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:51,573
Next time, guess who's back?

459
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:54,702
Noboru Kodo challenges Gao
to a dragon battle,

460
00:24:54,702 --> 00:24:57,121
but then that freak show
Ikazuchi turns up.

461
00:24:57,121 --> 00:25:01,417
Next episode, Unorthodox Arts,
Shoraiabare Kandachi!

462
00:25:01,417 --> 00:25:03,252
Join us for a Buddyfight!

